---
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '@/constants/app';
import Layout from '@/layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  description="How Miauudio handles local app data and optional web services."
  title="Miauudio Privacy Policy"
>
  <main>
    <a class="back" href="/">← Back to Miauudio</a>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: July 11, 2026</p>

    <p>
      Miauudio is a free ambient sound mixer developed by MichalMatu. This
      policy covers the Android app and the web/PWA version.
    </p>

    <h2>Data handled by the Android app</h2>
    <p>
      Miauudio does not require an account and does not include advertising or
      analytics. The developer does not receive your mixes, presets,
      favorites, settings, generator configurations, notes, todos, or imported
      audio. The Android app does not request internet access.
    </p>
    <p>
      Preferences are stored locally in the app's browser storage. Audio that
      you explicitly import is validated and copied into app-private storage.
      Imported files are not uploaded by Miauudio.
    </p>
    <p>
      Miauudio does not request health permissions, connect to Health Connect,
      or ask users to provide health data. It does not infer, transmit, or
      share health data. Miauudio is not a medical device and does not
      diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any medical condition.
    </p>

    <h2>Web/PWA features</h2>
    <p>
      The web version stores preferences locally in your browser. A shared mix
      is encoded in the fragment of the link that you choose to copy; URL
      fragments are not sent to the website host in HTTP requests. Imported
      audio is never included. Miauudio does not operate a server that receives
      those mixes.
    </p>
    <p>
      The optional Lofi Music Player is available only on the web. It connects
      to YouTube only after you press Continue. YouTube may then process data
      under Google's privacy policy. You can use the rest of Miauudio without
      enabling this feature.
    </p>

    <h2>Permissions and background playback</h2>
    <p>
      On Android, foreground-service and wake-lock permissions keep audio that
      you started playing active while the app is in the background or the
      screen is locked. An ongoing media notification makes playback visible
      and provides controls. The document picker gives Miauudio access only to
      a file you choose to import.
    </p>

    <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Local data remains until you delete it. Imported sounds can be deleted
      individually in My Sounds. Clearing Miauudio's app data or uninstalling
      the Android app removes its settings and private imported files. Clearing
      site data removes locally stored web preferences. The developer cannot
      delete this data remotely because the developer does not receive it.
    </p>
    <p>
      Miauudio excludes Android app data from cloud backup and device-to-device
      transfer. Links that you deliberately open from About & Privacy are
      handled by your system browser, and the destination may process data
      under its own privacy policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Sharing and sale</h2>
    <p>
      Miauudio does not sell personal data and the Android app does not share
      personal data with the developer or advertising companies.
    </p>

    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy questions, support, or feedback, email
      <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>. The repository
      issue tracker is currently disabled and is not a working contact route.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    width: min(760px, calc(100% - 40px));
    padding: 64px 0;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .back,
  main a {
    color: var(--color-foreground);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-top: 32px;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 7vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .updated {
    margin: 12px 0 32px;
    color: var(--color-foreground-subtle);
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 32px 0 8px;
    font-size: var(--font-md);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
</style>
